com.blockwithme.util.xtend.annotations

Class Processor<T extends org.eclipse.xtend.lib.macro.declaration.TypeDeclaration,M extends org.eclipse.xtend.lib.macro.declaration.MutableTypeDeclaration>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blockwithme.util.xtend.annotations.Processor<T,M>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TraceProcessor

    public class Processor<T extends org.eclipse.xtend.lib.macro.declaration.TypeDeclaration,M extends org.eclipse.xtend.lib.macro.declaration.MutableTypeDeclaration>
extends Object
    Base class for our own Processors (annotation-bound or not). The actual processor instances must have a public no-argument constructor.
    Author:
    monster
